  "summary": "Synthesized a boundary-Creator partition from the HelloWorld ATAK-touch inventories (4.10, 5.0, 5.1, 5.2-partial supplied; bands projected across 4.10..5.8). Every distinct ATAK type/member in the inventories is assigned to exactly one of ~44 Creators grouped by feature. The dominant crossing patterns are: (a) extends-base ATAK types (AbstractPlugin, AbstractPluginTool, DropDownReceiver, DropDownMapComponent, AbstractMapComponent, AbstractWidgetMapComponent, AbstractMapOverlay2, AbstractHierarchyListItem2, NavigationStackItem, Tool, AbstractMapItemSelectionTool, CotDetailHandler, MarkerDetailHandler, ContactConnectorManager.ContactConnectorHandler, ExportMarshal, ImportInternalSDResolver, TAKContactSender, ExtendedInfoView, CotStreamListener, AbstractLayer, GLAbstractLayer/GLAbstractLayer2, GLPointMapItem2, PluginPreferenceFragment) which become thin Humble shells subclassing the ATAK base and delegating to an ATAK-free Controller; (b) inbound ATAK->plugin listeners/SPIs/factories which become plugin-owned callback Ports; (c) live retained ATAK objects (MapView, MapItem/Marker/Shape/Route/MapGroup, Layer, GL* renderers, widgets, contacts, DropDown panes) referenced via opaque Handles; (d) immutable value types (GeoPoint/GeoBounds/GeoPointMetaData, CotEvent/CotDetail, Icon, NetConnectString, ConnectionEntry, Envelope, enums/const strings) crossing as plugin DTOs by value. Class-level surface is stable across 4.10..5.8 (the 4.10 inventory verified 0 class-level deltas vs 5.0 against main.jar), so the VAST MAJORITY of Creators are stable-all and their impls live in src/atakShared. Only two Creators carry a confirmed method-level break and split into compatibility bands at the 5.0->5.1 boundary: RadioCreator (RadioMapComponent.registerControl/unregisterControl gained a String key) and LayerDownloadCreator (RasterUtils.getCurrentImagery replaced by queryDatasets). RouteCreator has an additive 5.1 change (setLabels/setMetaMap) that is source-compatible and does not force a band. Highest re-verify risk (javap could not be run in any inventory environment): GLMapView public field access (scratch/idlHelper/currentPass), SensorFOV.setMetrics int-vs-float, CameraController.Programmatic arg order, GeoCalculations/PlacePointTool.MarkerCreator/DropDownReceiver.showDropDown overload sets, GLTexture.draw static-vs-instance \u2014 these should be byte-confirmed against each per-version main.jar before locking src/atakShared, and any confirmed delta promotes the owning Creator to a banded split."
}
